# Exploration: sed

## Rounds
  round 0: 39 isolated cumulative, 41 identical in round (single-phase)

## Observed: 23/24 flags
  3 solo, 20 via combination
  1 additional error-differentiated
  3 behavioral aliases detected

## Solo (unique behavior)
  --debug
    exemplar: "--debug" "input.txt" in words_minimal (different)
    base:
    flag:
      SED PROGRAM:
        i\nput.txt
  --follow-symlinks
    exemplar: "--follow-symlinks" "input.txt" "other.txt" in words_minimal (-2 lines)
    base:
      nput.txt
      hello world
    flag:
      nput.txt
      hello world
  --posix
    exemplar: "--posix" "$(head -n1 input.txt)" "input.txt" in passwd_minimal (+30 lines, exit 1→0)
    base:
      root:x:0:0:root:/root:/bin/bash
      daemon:x:1:1:daemon:/usr/sbin:/usr/sbin/nologin
      bin:x:2:2:bin:/bin:/usr/sbin/nologin
      sys:x:3:3:sys:/dev:/usr/sbin/nologin
      sync:x:4:65534:sync:/bin:/bin/sync
            ...
    flag:
      root:x:0:0:root:/root:/bin/bash
      daemon:x:1:1:daemon:/usr/sbin:/usr/sbin/nologin
      bin:x:2:2:bin:/bin:/usr/sbin/nologin
      sys:x:3:3:sys:/dev:/usr/sbin/nologin
      sync:x:4:65534:sync:/bin:/bin/sync
            ...
  -l
    exemplar: "-l" "input.txt" in words_minimal (different)
    base:
    flag:

